2. You will NOT ask "why var though" because the answer is "because i felt
   like it" and that should be enough for anyone.

3. If you find a bug, you have exactly two (2) options:
   a) Fix it and submit a PR like a civilized person
   b) Scream into the void and move on with your life
   Option C (complaining in my issues) is grounds for being mocked publicly.

4. The Signifer piece is NOT overpowered. This is non-negotiable. Do not
   email me about this. Do not open an issue. He is balanced. Trust.

5. If you make money off this somehow, honestly good for you??? i didnt
   think that was possible but go off king/queen/royalty.

6. You are legally encouraged (but not required) to add more chaos to
   this game. Add pieces. Remove pieces. Make the board 9x9. I dont
   care. The worse the idea the better.

7. If this game ruins a friendship, that is not my fault. Competitive
   chess-adjacent games have been destroying relationships since 1500.
   You were warned.

8. You may NOT use this code to train an AI that replaces me. The world
   only needs one person who writes javascript like a caffeinated squirrel
   and that person is ME.

9. Stalemate = loss. This is canon. This is law. This is gospel. If you
   fork this and change it to a draw, you are a coward and your fork
   is invalid.

10. If you actually read this entire license file, you have my respect.
